a moderate earthquake rattled southcentral 
utah today and seismologists said the temblor was an unusual late 
aftershock of a larger quake that struck the same area a month 
earlier 
the university of utah seismograph stations reported the quake 
measured 42 on the richter scale and was centered 16 miles 
