earthquake deaths last year nearly tripled the 
worlds annual average largely as a result of the tragic armenian 
tremor the us geological survey reported monday 
the years loss of life in earth tremors was the worst in more 
than a decade and occurred despite a decline in the total number of 
significant earthquales reported during the year survey officials 
reported 
the exact number of deaths remains unknown but is likely nearly 
triple the average annual toll of about 10000 fatalities worldwide 
a year earlier in 1987 only 1100 lives had been lost in 
earthquakes 
