900 cargo doors in its fleet of 399 aircraft including boeing 727s 
737s 747s and dc10s made by mcdonnell douglas corp 
the seven repairs included repairing a 2inch crack in the 
doorframe of a 737 replacing a doorstop on a 737 replacing two 
small brackets on a 747 latch mechanism and adjusting a dc10 motor 
the statement said 
all of these repairs would have been performed in the 
normal course of maintenance the statement said of more than 
1700 daily united flights only two delays and one cancellation 
were necessary 
