states borders march 1 to states seeking to dispose of hazardous 
waste in south carolina that they wont dispose of themselves 
as of monday 27 states had not responded to the state department 
of health and environmental controls request for information needed 
to enact campbells order officials said 
the order affects the massive gsx hazardous waste landfill in 
sumter county east of columbia which now holds close to a billion 
pounds of hazardous waste about 70 percent of it from out of state 
the site is one of only two commercial hazardous waste landfills in 
the southeast and accepts roughly 135000 tons of chemical garbage 
annually the other site is in alabama 
state health officials sent letters to all 50 states and puerto 
rico informing them of campbells order and asking for information 
on their waste handling laws by feb 15 
but by monday afternoon only 23 states had responded 
