<TEXT>
neonazis are preparing 
commemorations on the 100th anniversary of adolf hitlers birth next 
month and west german officials are bracing for possible outbreaks 
of rightist violence 
the nazi dictator was born april 20 1889 in the austrian 
village of braunau just over the border from bavaria 
this is the most important event weve had in a long time 
said michael kuehnen west german neonazi leader 
the preparations come as west germans warily eye a rise in 
extremerightist sentiments in their country in january for 
example the republican party made a strong showing in west berlins 
elections by calling for the expulsion of foreigners and 
asylumseekers 
neonazis from several countries are expected at the european 
hitler convention specifically designed to commemorate the 
dictators 100th birthday but kuehnen declined to specify exactly 
when or where it will take place 
we dont want to give the country time to gear up to prevent 
it he said but added that spain or scandinavia were possible 
places federal law bars such a meeting in west germany although 
kuehnen promises smaller birthday commemorations in the frankfurt 
area 
the neonazi leader who often wears a brown shirt and black 
pants said the number of participants at the hitler convention 
could range from 1000 to several thousand depending on the 
location 
kuehnen whose organizing committee even has a logo with the 
initials ah in the center insisted there will be no organized 
violence on the hitler anniversary 
but we arent responsible for every young person and every 
soccer rowdy the 33yearold neonazi added in a telephone 
interview fringe groups espousing neonazi and rightist beliefs 
occasionally disturb professional soccer games in west germany 
kuehnen who has spent more than seven years in prison for 
neonazi activities has set up an office in frankfurt to organize 
the birthday event with the help of his followers hes hoping 
neonazis and rightwing extremists from spain france denmark 
belgium and norway as well as west germany will attend the european 
convention 
although the birthday falls in april there were reports as early 
as january about plans for an observance in the west german news 
media 
the newsmagazine der spiegel said on jan 30 that this years 
celebrations are meant to attract public attention and distribute 
propaganda in contrast to previous years 
in the past rightwing extremist cronies drank to the fuehrer 
in the back rooms of german bars and in hotels of hitlers austrian 
birthplace of braunau der spiegel noted 
braunau itself was the site of a clash between neonazis and 
procommunists on hitlers 90th birthday in 1979 
this past jan 22 the conservative welt am sonntag newspaper 
said officials already were bracing for acts of violence and that 
jews and foreigners were possible targets 
matthias strohs a spokesman on internal security issues for the 
badenwuerttemberg state interior ministry agrees that trouble 
could break out 
theres no question you can count on acts of violence he 
said the possible targets range from foreigners to german 
officials and allied military installations 
allies france britain and the united states drew the neonazis 
wrath for keeping rudolf hess hitlers deputy in prison until he 
died in what was officially determined as a suicide in 1987 
although the soviets were primarily responsible for rejecting pleas 
for clemency 
strohs speaking by telephone from his office in stuttgart said 
vandalism and pronazi slogans painted on walls were also a 
possibility around the time of the birthday 
the spokesman said officials assume oldergeneration nazis will 
also commemorate hitlers birthday but in a much less public way 
the older ones are much more careful in the way they act 
strohs said they wont make such a spectacle out in the public 
it will be more of an internal affair 
alfons metzger spokesman for the bavarian interior ministry also 
said violence cant be ruled out as a possibility on the hitler 
birthday and that police are alerted to it 
several smaller neonazi groups also routinely celebrate hitlers 
birthday and are expected to do so again this year federal 
officials say there are about 28300 rightwing extremists in this 
country of 613 million people 
the deutsche volksunion german peoples union identified by 
federal authorities as west germanys largest rightwing extremist 
organization has totally disassociated itself from the hitler 
commemorations 
we are convinced that on april 20 1989 there will be several 
birthday celebrations for hitler said bernd droese spokesman for 
the party which claims a membership of 25000 fifty percent of 
them will take place in loony bins where some people assert they 
are the reincarnation of the fuehrer 
the other 50 percent will be organized by agents and 
provocateurs who want to let the specter of the fuehrer ghost wander 
around 
