religious and secular jews a problem that dogs his personal life 
with avital 
mrs sharansky is religious and he is not making them an odd 
couple in a country where secular and religious jews usually live in 
separate neighborhoods 
sharansky thinks religion should be a private matter and lashes 
out at newspaper gossip speculating his marriage could fall apart 
because of religious differences 
i feel like my own bald pate has been conscripted into israels 
kulturkampf or culture war sharansky says people here 
concentrate too much on their differences you have to concentrate 
instead on principles and common aims 
mine and avitals ways about religion are very different i am 
not religious but there are some things i accept that help us build 
a family what i do basically is to observe the jewish teaching of 
maintaining domestic tranquility 
sharansky is also critical of the acrimony and horsetrading 
among the 15 political parties in israels 120member parliament 
id like to see more mutual values and consensus in israel 
he says it also upsets me to see people sacrificing principles 
the most disappointing thing is the intolerance in society with 
that we will have to deal 
sharansky says that one of his problems in coping with what is 
going on in isreal is getting used to having so many choices and 
shades of differences after fighting for so many years against the 
oneparty system in the soviet union 
after you fight a world which is black and white and you know 
exactly what you want and you dont compromise with evil you come 
to the free world where the choices are tremendous and the colors 
are very numerous he says 
one of the multicolored issues sharansky has trouble dealing with 
is the palestinian problem his views are a vague fusion of a 
conservative loyalty to his new country and an overall concern for 
human rights 
during the palestinian uprising in the occupied west bank and 
gaza strip sharansky has researched israels controversial jailing 
practices which allow imprisonment without trial and complicated 
regulations governing when soldiers may shoot at protesters 
he speaks defensively about what he has learned 
i spoke to leading army people about instructions to soldiers 
about opening fire he says you cannot imagine how many cases 
there are where this is forbidden the poor soldiers cant even keep 
track of all the rules 
because of the nature of this country there are serious human 
rights problems like in every country but a democracy has 
instruments to deal with these problems we have developed a system 
of selfchecks 
before the uprising sharansky also met with palestinian leaders 
in the occupied territories such as faisal husseini of east 
jerusalem but he curtailed most of these contacts after sharp 
public accusations that he was consorting with the plo 
sharansky has resisted pressures from arab groups seeking his 
support by trying to draw a comparision between their struggle for a 
palestinian state and the fight for jewish emigration from the 
soviet union 
to say that because sharansky was against the soviet union this 
should make him against the israeli government this isnt true 
sharansky says there is no parallel between them they are two 
principally different things 
