the states vegetable farmers surveyed heavy 
losses in tomato cucumber and potato crops monday after a 
recordsetting cold snap but an industry official predicted 
shoppers will not face shortages 
wayne crain marketingproduction manager for the florida fruit 
and vegetable association predicted that supermarket consumers 
would see little loss of volume in popular vegetables such as 
lettuce and tomatoes despite damage to winter and early spring crops 
we still have plenty of product were still in the market 
crain said 
