<TEXT>
the board of directors of morton thiokol inc on 
monday authorized management to proceed with a plan for a taxfree 
spinoff of the companys commercial operations officials said 
the action will create a new company morton international inc 
consisting of specialty chemicals air bag manufacturing and salt 
businesses 
the aerospace business which manufactures the space shuttle 
booster motor and strategic and tactical propulsion systems will 
continue to operate within the existing corporate entity which will 
be renamed thiokol corp 
the transaction is expected to be finalized july 1 subject to an 
internal revenue service ruling that it is taxfree and to the 
approval of stockholders said company spokesman tom russell 
morton thiokol stockholders will receive a shareforshare 
distribution of morton international stock russell said management 
believes the stock of both companies will qualify for listing on the 
new york stock exchange the board will establish record and payment 
dates for the stock distribution later 
this move separates two businesses with distinct financial 
investment and operating characteristics so that each can adopt 
strategies and pursue objectives appropriate to its specific 
businesses said charles s locke morton thiokols chairman and 
chief executive officer 
the transaction will allow investors to evaluate better the 
individual businesses and their future outlook enhancing the 
likelihood that the true value of each business will be properly 
reflected he said 
locke said the combined market values of the stocks of the two 
companies may exceed the recent market value of morton thiokol stock 
morton thiokol stock closed monday at 40 in consolidated new 
york stock exchange trading unchanged from fridays close 
locke said the combination of the specialty chemicals inflatable 
restraint systems or air bags and salt businesses will create a 
company with fiscal year 1989 sales approaching 15 billion assets 
of 14 billion and over 8000 employees 
it is expected that locke and s jay stewart president and chief 
operating officer of morton thiokol will be elected to those posts 
at morton international 
locke said thiokol will be a company with approximately 11 
billion in sales assets of 800 million and more than 12000 
employees ed garrison group vice president for aerospace in ogden 
utah is expected to be elected president and chief operating 
officer while a search for a chairman and chief executive officer 
is anticipated 
russell said the action had nothing to do with the aerospace 
groups 500 million redesign of the space shuttle booster in the 
wake of the 1986 challenger explosion 
the redesigned booster which corrected joint problems blamed for 
the blast has been used successfully on two shuttle flights in 
recent months and will be used on several more 
the shuttle program is in very good shape were very confident 
of redesign russell said 
he said the chicagobased company was preparing to bid on a 2 
billionplus contract for 66 new flights sets of two boosters each 
and 10 development motors 
the company said that under the spin off the combined dividends 
initially paid by the two companies will equal the current morton 
thiokol dividend 
the company plans to redeem its 8 percent debentures due in 1995 
and 9 percent debentures due in 2000 prior to june 30 1989 
although the business momentum and profitability outlook for 
morton thiokol is unchanged from a previous projection of an 
earningspershare increase to a range of 340 to 360 for the 
fiscal year ending june 30 the company expects that significant 
special charges associated with the spinoff will reduce profit below 
that range 
since the operating results of morton international and thiokol 
will be reported separately for the quarter and fiscal year ending 
june 30 no revised projection is being made for morton thiokol 
